root.publications: Evans, Nicholas. 1990. The Minkin Language of the Burketown Region. In Geoffrey N O'Grady & Darrell T Tryon (eds.), Studies in Comparative Pama-Nyungan, 173-207. Canberra: Pacific Linguistics.

child.pub-comments: "…to the west and south-west are the co-dialects Yukulta and Nguburindi. Together with Yangkaal, Kayardild and Lardil, spoken in the various Wellesley Islands these make up the Tangkic group. In terms of vocabulary, Tangkic can be divided into two 'languages' - Lardil on the one hand, and the remaining Tangkic dialects (Yukulta, Nguburindi, Yangkaal and Kayardild) on the other. However, grammatical differences suggest a further subdivision, with Yukulta and Nguburindi in one group, and Yangkaal and Kayardild on the other" (Evans 1990: 174).
child.publications: Evans, Nicholas. 1990. The Minkin Language of the Burketown Region. In Geoffrey N O'Grady & Darrell T Tryon (eds.), Studies in Comparative Pama-Nyungan, 173-207. Canberra: Pacific Linguistics.
